In Table 2, we report the results from our experiments on the review-volume prediction task. We observe that metapaths with nodes containing categorical attributes perform significantly better than vector-based features. In particular, categorical attributes like Cuisines, Facilities, and Price have a significantly higher coefficient of determination (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
